TopicTitle: Starlion Industries - KSPI & IFS Compatibility Patches for Fueltanks, Spaceplanes, & more [CKAN]

Articles.Content:
Hmmm.... at the moment, I have a single patch applying to all relevant parts. This allows me to also alter relevant parts from any part-pack. If I am to remove the Helium-4 from all but a few parts, I would prefer to some reasonable criteria to do so (like by cost, mass, etc.) This would be very tricky to implement in a useful way, as I am not directly choosing what part gets what, doing as you suggest would be very tricky at best.

As it is, as of the next update, Argon & Xenon will be stored cryogenically when Realfuels or MFT is installed. This will mean that those modes require power, but have a greater amount of fuel stored. If one wants to have a pressurized tank for them, the MFT-tanks will be available (so each has an advantage). As such, the RF/MFT-less mode will retain them in pressurized form, as not to inconvenience those players.

After that, I am going to recalculate the amount of each other resource my patch provides, using the amount of LiquidHydrogen as the baseline (I will be assuming amount is in Liters, unless Freethinker informs me otherwise).
New Kerbalstuff URL is https://kerbalstuff.com/mod/1080/KSPI%20Integration%20Patch%20Set. (OP updated). I removed the Star-Trek engines link for now, needs heavy updating.

Could you tell me what, if any, of Realfuels & Modular Fuel Tanks you have installed? The turbojets should only have ATM until they are upgraded. the main KSPI has been rebalancing and fixing various upgrade nodes. the upgrade tech for turbojets to use all fuels is now Experimental Aircraft Engines [expAircraftEngines].
Note that in the latest release a new property called jetPerformanceProfile is added. It determines how the Atmospheric Thermal Propulsion performs as a Ramjet (= 0) or TurboJet (=1) .
